Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.960
Hi! Today I`m going to make Hadik. It is usually made by Muslim women in Ashura.

00:00:06.140 --> 00:00:08.220
green lentils - 1/2 glass

00:00:08.893 --> 00:00:11.093
wheat - 1 glass

00:00:15.573 --> 00:00:17.913
mung beans - 1/2 glass

00:00:20.888 --> 00:00:23.328
dry maize - 1/2 glass

00:00:25.160 --> 00:00:27.720
black eyed bean - 1/2 glass

00:00:29.201 --> 00:00:32.101
chick-pea -1/2 glass

00:00:35.209 --> 00:00:37.949
cranberry bean - 1/2 glass

00:00:39.518 --> 00:00:43.898
You should wash all ingredients and pour water over them

00:00:46.514 --> 00:01:03.254
In the morning just pour off water, add cold water and boil every ingredient in separate dishes

00:01:04.020 --> 00:01:27.480
You should gather foam with a spoon

00:01:28.294 --> 00:02:04.634
Boil all ingredients 

00:02:06.053 --> 00:02:09.933
Wheat and it`s water pour in a deep dish.

00:02:10.360 --> 00:02:15.460
But pour off water other ingredients, wash them in cold water

00:02:19.140 --> 00:02:42.540
And add to wheat mass maize, then chick-pea, cranberry bean, mung bean

00:02:50.360 --> 00:02:55.300
blacked eyed bean and green lentils

00:03:05.540 --> 00:03:23.800
Add 5 glasses of hot water, boil all ingredients 10-15 minutes

00:03:25.346 --> 00:03:28.273
Hadik is made in Ashura day but till 12 am. Besides of it you can make halwa in this day.

00:03:28.940 --> 00:03:32.320
